{"id":14880948,"mediaExerciseId":"905135ea-abda-4916-94b0-ae420e12de4e","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":184,"solutions":[{"id":5966529,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will determine the cost of an insurance policy; if the payment each year is $35,000, the term is forever, and the rate of return is 4.7%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Since the period has no end, to calculate the policy's value, we will use the present value of perpetuity to determine the value of the policy. The present value perpetuity can be computed using the following formula:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Present Value of Perpetuity} &=\\dfrac{\\text{Cash amount}}{\\text{Rate}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Given the following information:\n\n| | | \n|--|--| \n|Cash amount |$35,000 | \n|Rate |4.7% | \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":201,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/d550b80b91ed5ebe5d992b488955a51b/fc2eee4fc9b343d69a39587733228c71/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":101,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/d550b80b91ed5ebe5d992b488955a51b/fc2eee4fc9b343d69a39587733228c71/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now calculate the policy's value using the perpetuity present value.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Present Value of Perpetuity} &= \\dfrac{\\text{\\$35,000}}{.047}\n\\\\[10pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\bf\\$744,680.86}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**Therefore, the cost of the policy, which should correspond with its value, is $744,680.86**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"8cfb7e5b-a105-4682-b696-1aee05f78e28","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880949,"exerciseName":"11","page":184,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f5a3f9b8-e748-426a-9464-906137c23dbb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-11-f5a3f9b8-e748-426a-9464-906137c23dbb"},{"id":14880950,"exerciseName":"12","page":184,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f68e1a78-4603-458e-adf1-a51b27de10b0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-12-f68e1a78-4603-458e-adf1-a51b27de10b0"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880947,"exerciseName":"9","page":184,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7ded33c8-6e68-4699-8258-264045784ed2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-9-7ded33c8-6e68-4699-8258-26404578